"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"Major"},"27":{"id":"/docs/changelog-25","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"Update!"},"28":{"id":"/docs/changelog-26","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"This is the biggest update yet by far. The entire library has been migrated to a monorepo structure with scoped packages, allowing for framework specific exports, additional optimizations, and more! Framework specific exports is also the next big feature I'm working on."},"29":{"id":"/docs/changelog-27","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"As such, the name of the package has changed, gone is `toomanycharts` and in is `@jgmc/...`!"},"30":{"id":"/docs/changelog-28","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"Previously all functionality lived under `toomanycharts`, but now the math & framework agnostic code lives in `@jgmc/core`. Additionally I had one single dependency in-use for creating charts `linkedom` which is a fantastic library, but as part of this move I've removed it & am now just using strings!"},"31":{"id":"/docs/changelog-29","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"This has allowed for a `3x` speed increase, a smaller bundle size, and means aside from the `@jgmc/core` package there are now zero dependencies! Additionally strings are incredibly flexible, so right out of the box `@jgmc/vanilla` is completely SSR compatible, and can technically be used anywhere you can use a string!"},"32":{"id":"/docs/changelog-30","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"That being said framework specific exports are still on the way, so that framework strengths can be properly utilized, but in the meantime you can use `@jgmc/vanilla` in any framework, and it's already SSR compatible!"},"33":{"id":"/docs/changelog-31","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"Not only that but aside from a few exceptions, everything should work pretty much the same in terms of usage, aside from the output."},"34":{"id":"/docs/changelog-32","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"installation moved!"},"35":{"id":"/docs/changelog-33","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"`toomanycharts` is now `@jgmc/vanilla`"},"36":{"id":"/docs/changelog-34","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"`@jgmc/core` for math & framework agnostic code"},"37":{"id":"/docs/changelog-35","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"removed `linkedom` dependency, now just using strings for charts"},"38":{"id":"/docs/changelog-36","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"all charts under `@jgmc/vanilla` return strings"},"39":{"id":"/docs/changelog-37","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#023","content":"Removed `classes` option from all charts"},"40":{"id":"/docs/changelog-38","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#023","content":"replacing with sensible default classes applied to chart elements"},"41":{"id":"/docs/changelog-39","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#023","content":"See Charts Classes for more info"},"42":{"id":"/docs/changelog-40","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#022","content":"After a long break I came back and finished up the initial implementation of the `asciiBarchart` I'd been working on. While I plan to continue with ASCII chart types I felt there was still plenty more worthwhile things to add in to SVG charts. The big one being two very common chart types - pie & donut charts! Those have both been added."},"43":{"id":"/docs/changelog-41","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#022","content":"Next up I will be doing some cleanup / refinement of the codebase. Standardizing some things across chart types, doing some type naming adjustments, etc... You can check the `TODO.md` in the repo for specifics."},"44":{"id":"/docs/changelog-42","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#022","content":"After cleanup & refinement I'll be doing work on getting framework specific exports working."},"45":{"id":"/docs/changelog-43","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#022","content":"`piechart`"},"46":{"id":"/docs/changelog-44","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#022","content":"`donutchart`"},"47":{"id":"/docs/changelog-45","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#022","content":"Experimental features are features that are in the early stages of development, and may be subject to change or removal without a major version bump."},"48":{"id":"/docs/changelog-46","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#022","content":"`asciiBarchart`"},"49":{"id":"/docs/changelog-47","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#021","content":"`colors` is now `fillColors`"},"50":{"id":"/docs/changelog-48","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#021","content":"Added `strokeColors` to `barchart` and `barchartStacked`"},"51":{"id":"/docs/changelog-49","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#021","content":"Added `strokeWidths` to `barchart` and `barchartStacked`"},"52":{"id":"/docs/changelog-50","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#020","content":"Revamped label